    <item>
      <title>Python for hackers: paramiko</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/2022/09/python-for-hackers-paramiko/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 26 Sep 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/2022/09/python-for-hackers-paramiko/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;python-for-hackersparamiko&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;strong&gt;Python for hackers: paramiko&lt;/strong&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#python-for-hackersparamiko&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*cHmfmYLtoze7wtcUFY5BVA.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Introduction&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Hello, in this article, we will get to know the &lt;em&gt;paramiko&lt;/em&gt; module that allows us to establish SSH connections with Python.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;what-is-paramiko&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  What is paramiko?&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#what-is-paramiko&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SSH&lt;/strong&gt; (Secure Shell) is a cryptographic network protocol used for secure operation of network services over an unsecured network. With SSH, you can connect to and manage your network devices, Linux and Windows machines. It works on port 22 by default.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Python:socket for hackers</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/2022/09/pythonsocket-for-hackers/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 21 Sep 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/2022/09/pythonsocket-for-hackers/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;pythonsocket-for-hackers&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;strong&gt;Python:socket for hackers&lt;/strong&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#pythonsocket-for-hackers&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*Z3ieIgd5w_LPy0R2bLu6pg.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Introduction&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Hello, in this article, we will get to know the socket module that we can use to connect to the IP and port addresses of remote servers.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;what-is-a-socket&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  What is a socket?&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#what-is-a-socket&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html#module-socket&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Socket&lt;/a&gt; is a module that comes installed with Python. Thanks to this module, we can connect to the desired IP and port address. Now let&amp;rsquo;s take a look at how to use this module and what we can do with it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Python for hackers: selenium</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/2022/09/python-for-hackers-selenium/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 02 Sep 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/2022/09/python-for-hackers-selenium/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;python-for-hackersselenium&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;strong&gt;Python for hackers: selenium&lt;/strong&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#python-for-hackersselenium&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*0uUmJ2J01vpcie8grd91Yw.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Introduction&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Hello, in this article, we will get to know the selenium module, which allows us to perform operations on websites like a user.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;what-is-selenium&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  What is Selenium?&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#what-is-selenium&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://selenium-python.readthedocs.io/&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Selenium&lt;/a&gt; is a web automation library. With Selenium we can visit and interact with a website.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Python for hackers: requests</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/2022/08/python-for-hackers-requests/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 Aug 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/2022/08/python-for-hackers-requests/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;python-for-hackersrequests&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Python for Hackers: requests&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#python-for-hackersrequests&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*a87phGSd-sbfiJLWPfGMxA.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  Introduction&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Hello, in this article, we will get to know Python&amp;rsquo;s &lt;em&gt;requests&lt;/em&gt; module, where we can write tools in the field of web application security.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;What is ###requests?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://requests.readthedocs.io/&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;requests&lt;/a&gt; is a simple but elegant HTTP module of Python. It allows you to send HTTP requests extremely easily. For requests made with the GET method, you do not need to manually add query strings to your URLs or formally encode your POST data, the requests module takes care of these tasks for you. In this article, we will write various web tools with &lt;em&gt;requests&lt;/em&gt;, but let&amp;rsquo;s take a look at the installation first. We assume that you have a basic knowledge of the Python language and continue. If you want, you can also look at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://pwnlab.me/intermediate-python-articles/&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;articles&lt;/a&gt; about Python on our website.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
